00:30:56.870 --> 00:31:00.000
Let's say you don't
like it so much.

00:31:00.000 --> 00:31:00.670
You should like it.

00:31:00.670 --> 00:31:04.320
But let's say, they don't
like it so much.

00:31:04.320 --> 00:31:07.630
And so there is some cost of
using more protection.

00:31:07.630 --> 00:31:11.230
But the advantage of condoms is
that you're less likely to

00:31:11.230 --> 00:31:14.530
get an STD, and you're less
likely to get pregnant.

00:31:14.530 --> 00:31:19.280
And then what people look at
is the cost and benefits of

00:31:19.280 --> 00:31:23.720
pregnancy, of a pregnancy
now, as a teenager.

00:31:23.720 --> 00:31:25.930
And the cost of an STD.

00:31:25.930 --> 00:31:28.930
There is no benefit
of getting an STD.

00:31:28.930 --> 00:31:31.730
And the probability that they
might get pregnant and the

00:31:31.730 --> 00:31:33.760
probability that they
might get an STD.

00:31:33.760 --> 00:31:37.030
And the cost and benefit of
pregnancy is the value of

00:31:37.030 --> 00:31:39.000
having the child.

00:31:39.000 --> 00:31:41.640
You might like to have a child
more if you have partner to

00:31:41.640 --> 00:31:44.700
have a child with then if you
have to raise them alone.

00:31:44.700 --> 00:31:48.140
So the value of a child in
marriage might be higher than

00:31:48.140 --> 00:31:50.810
the value of a child with
a casual partner.

00:31:50.810 --> 00:31:54.450
And then on the cost side is
foregone earnings, because if

00:31:54.450 --> 00:31:57.500
you have child, you have
to take of the child.

00:31:57.500 --> 00:31:59.040
